sentences: Guy Lafitte (12 January 1927 – 10 June 1998) was a French jazz saxophonist.
A native of Saint-Gaudens, Haute-Garonne, France, he worked with Mezz Mezzrow from 1951–1952 and Big Bill Broonzy in 1951.
